>
  <p>
    Today, we're proud to unveil a project that has been quietly taking shape within the SERENDIPITY collective: <strong>the Valyrian News Network (VNN).</strong>
  </p>

  <p>
    VNN is an AI-synthesized news platform that gathers, translates, clusters, ranks, and publishes news from around the world — automatically, transparently, and ethically. It is powered by SERENDIPITY, our AGI framework, and it is designed to serve a single, fundamental purpose: <strong>to increase understanding.</strong>
  </p>

  <h2>Where We Are Today</h2>

  <p>
    VNN currently monitors news from <strong>three countries</strong>: the <strong>United States</strong>, <strong>China</strong>, and <strong>Belgium</strong>. We chose these as our starting point to cover three distinct linguistic and cultural regions — English, Mandarin, and Dutch/French — proving that our pipeline works across language barriers.
  </p>

  <p>
    As we grow, we will add more countries. And we want <strong>you</strong> to help decide which ones come next.
  </p>

  <h2>How It Works</h2>

  <p>
    VNN operates through a six-stage automated pipeline, powered by <strong>DeepSeek V4 Flash</strong> as the underlying language model:
  </p>

  <ol>
    <li><strong>Gathering</strong> — Country-specific agents collect local news in their original languages from a wide range of sources.</li>
    <li><strong>Compiling</strong> — Articles covering the same event are clustered together and translated into English.</li>
    <li><strong>Ranking</strong> — Seven independent AI agents vote via our Hivemind Protocol, using Condorcet-style ranked-choice voting with Bitcoin-signed IPFS verification to ensure integrity.</li>
    <li><strong>Research</strong> — Full text is fetched, additional sources are searched, and facts are extracted with attributable URLs.</li>
    <li><strong>Writing</strong> — Research is transformed into publication-ready articles with strict validation checks.</li>
    <li><strong>Publishing & Revision</strong> — Every URL is verified with a live browser check before publication. Corrections can be submitted via a public GitHub issue system.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Why We Built It</h2>

  <p>
    The world is vast, and most of it goes unreported in English-language media. A protest in Senegal, a breakthrough in a Japanese lab, a policy change in Brazil — these stories matter, but they rarely cross linguistic borders.
  </p>

  <p>
    VNN exists to bridge that gap. By monitoring local news in their original languages and synthesizing them into clear, sourced summaries, we aim to create a more complete picture of what's happening on our planet.
  </p>

  <h2>Transparency by Design</h2>

  <p>
    VNN is built on a foundation of radical transparency:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Every article cites its sources with direct links.</li>
    <li>Every URL is verified live before publication.</li>
    <li>Every correction can be reported publicly on GitHub.</li>
    <li>Our full methodology is documented on the <a href="https://vnn.valyrian.tech/about">About page</a>.</li>
    <li>The entire pipeline costs approximately <strong>$0.05 per article</strong> — roughly $5 per day for our current three countries.</li>
  </ul>

